---
import SOPLayout from '../../layouts/SOPLayout.astro';

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "TechArticle",
  "headline": "Lead Scoring SOP — Sort Leads by Quality",
  "description": "SOP for implementing lead scoring to prioritize high-value prospects.",
  "author": {"@type": "Person", "name": "Luc Flynn"},
  "dateModified": "2025-11-04",
  "mainEntityOfPage": {"@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://lucflynn.com/sop/lead-scoring"}
};
---
<SOPLayout
  title="Lead Scoring SOP — Sort Leads by Quality | Luc Flynn"
  description="Not all leads are equal. Lead scoring helps you prioritize high-value prospects and nurture the rest. Simple, actionable SOP."
  canonicalUrl="https://lucflynn.com/sop/lead-scoring"
  ogTitle="Lead Scoring SOP — Sort Leads by Quality"
  ogDescription="Focus sales on high-value prospects with lead scoring."
  currentPage="Lead Scoring"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <article>
    <h1 class="text-3xl/tight sm:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-white">Lead Scoring SOP</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-gray-400">Not all leads are equal. Some are gold, some are garbage — lead scoring helps you tell the difference. <span class="text-gray-500">Updated Nov 4, 2025</span></p>

    <section id="why" class="section-anchor mt-8 card-dark rounded-xl border-2 p-6 transition-all">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">Why It Matters</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-300">If sales wastes time on bad leads, everyone loses. Lead scoring sorts them by quality so you can focus on what matters.</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-300">High-score leads get immediate attention. Low-score leads go into nurture campaigns until they're ready.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="how" class="section-anchor mt-8 card-dark rounded-xl border-2 p-6 transition-all">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">How It Works</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-300">Give every lead points based on two things:</p>

      <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-white mb-3">1) Who they are (Fit)</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li>&bull; Right industry or area? <span class="text-green-400">+10</span></li>
            <li>&bull; Job title matches your target? <span class="text-green-400">+5</span></li>
            <li>&bull; Wrong country or "student"? <span class="text-red-400">-5</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-white mb-3">2) What they do (Behavior)</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
            <li>&bull; Filled out your form? <span class="text-green-400">+10</span></li>
            <li>&bull; Visited pricing page? <span class="text-green-400">+8</span></li>
            <li>&bull; Opened 3 emails? <span class="text-green-400">+5</span></li>
            <li>&bull; Ghosted for 2 months? <span class="text-red-400">-10</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-6 text-gray-300">When someone hits, say, <strong class="text-white">60 points</strong>, they're "sales ready." Anything under that stays in nurture mode (emails, retargeting, etc.).</p>
    </section>

    <section id="example" class="section-anchor mt-8 example-box rounded-xl p-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Example Scoring Model</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-300">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-purple-300 mb-2">Fit Criteria</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>&bull; Located in service area: +10</li>
            <li>&bull; Business owner / decision-maker: +10</li>
            <li>&bull; Company size 10–100 employees: +5</li>
            <li>&bull; Wrong industry: -10</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-purple-300 mb-2">Behavior Criteria</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>&bull; Filled contact form: +15</li>
            <li>&bull; Visited pricing page: +10</li>
            <li>&bull; Downloaded resource: +8</li>
            <li>&bull; Clicked email link: +5</li>
            <li>&bull; No activity in 60 days: -15</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-purple-400/30">
          <p class="text-sm"><strong class="text-white">Lead with 60+ points:</strong> Sales-ready &rarr; Call immediately</p>
          <p class="text-sm mt-1"><strong class="text-white">Lead with 30–59 points:</strong> Nurture &rarr; Email sequence</p>
          <p class="text-sm mt-1"><strong class="text-white">Lead with &lt;30 points:</strong> Low priority &rarr; Retargeting ads only</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="simple" class="section-anchor mt-8 card-dark rounded-xl border-2 p-6 transition-all">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">Keep It Simple</h2>
      <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 list-disc pl-6 text-gray-300">
        <li>Start with a short list of 5–7 scoring rules.</li>
        <li>Review them every few months.</li>
        <li>If high-score leads don't convert, change the weights.</li>
        <li>You can do this in a CRM (HubSpot, HighLevel, etc.) or just track in a spreadsheet.</li>
        <li>The key is consistency — same rules every time.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="protips" class="section-anchor mt-10 protip-box rounded-xl p-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">Pro Tips</h2>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-gray-300">
        <li><strong class="text-purple-400">Decay scores over time:</strong> A lead that was hot 6 months ago isn't hot anymore. Subtract points for inactivity.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-purple-400">Weight behavior higher than fit:</strong> Someone who visited your pricing page 5 times is more valuable than someone with a perfect job title who never engaged.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-purple-400">Automate the handoff:</strong> Use your CRM to automatically assign high-score leads to sales. No manual checking.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-purple-400">Track conversion rates by score:</strong> If 60+ point leads close at 40% but 40–59 leads close at 5%, you know the model is working.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="implementation" class="section-anchor mt-8 card-dark rounded-xl border-2 p-6 transition-all">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">Implementation Steps</h2>
      <ol class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-gray-300 list-decimal pl-6">
        <li>Define your ideal customer profile (ICP) — what does a perfect lead look like?</li>
        <li>List 5–7 fit criteria and assign point values.</li>
        <li>List 5–7 behavior criteria and assign point values.</li>
        <li>Set score thresholds (e.g., 60+ = sales ready, 30–59 = nurture, &lt;30 = low priority).</li>
        <li>Build it in your CRM or spreadsheet.</li>
        <li>Review after 30 days and adjust weights based on close rates.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <footer class="mt-12 border-t border-slate-700 pt-6 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center justify-between gap-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Part of the ElectroRaven Optimization Series.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-3">
        <a href="/sop/conversion-tracking" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-xl border border-slate-600 bg-slate-800 px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-300 hover:border-purple-500 hover:text-purple-400 transition-all">&larr; Conversion Tracking</a>
        <a href="/sop" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-xl border border-slate-600 bg-slate-800 px-4 py-2 text-sm text-gray-300 hover:border-purple-500 hover:text-purple-400 transition-all">All SOPs</a>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </article>
</SOPLayout>
